Who Rufillus and Garg onius (which name appears as Gorgo- nius in the old editions) may have been we cannot tell. ssat they were persons of some note Orelli infers from the fact that Horace’s ridicule of them had made him enemies, as appears from the passage quoted above from the fourth Satire.
